        <LEXMeaning Id="002953001003000" IsBiblicalTerm="M" EntryCode="1.4" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Geographical Objects and Features</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSubDomains>
            <LEXSubDomain>Universe, Creation</LEXSubDomain>
          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-10-27 10:20:52" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the universe as the product of God’s activity in creation</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>universe</Gloss>
                <Gloss>creation</Gloss>
                <Gloss>what was made</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The meaning of κτίσις[c] might very well be treated as a simple derivative of the verb {L:κτίζω&lt;SDBG:κτίζω:000000&gt;} ‘to create’ ({D:42.35}), since the reference is to the result of God’s creative act. However, in a number of contexts, the process of creation is no longer focal, and what is in focus is the total physical universe. In some languages the meaning may be best expressed as ‘the world and all that is in it’ or even ‘everything that exists.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
